The '''NSW Education Standards Authority''' (NESA) is the state government education board in [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]. It was formed on 1&nbsp;January&nbsp;2017 replacing the [[Board of Studies, Teaching and Educational Standards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/nsw/new-education-authority-in-nsw-with-power-to-close-schools-and-run-inspections-20160819-gqwk2d.html|title=A new, beefed-up authority will have power to close schools in NSW|first=Kelsey|last=Munro|date=19 August 2016|work=smh.com.au|accessdate=19 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NEW EDUCATION STANDARDS AUTHORITY FOR NSW|url=http://news.bostes.nsw.edu.au/blog/2016/12/20/new-education-standards-authority-for-nsw|website=bostes.nsw.edu.au|date=20 December 2016}}</ref>
NESA sets and monitors quality teaching, learning, assessment and school standards. This includes responsibility, across NSW public, Catholic and independent schools, for: *kindergarten to Year 12 curriculum *accreditation of teachers and teaching degrees *the internationally recognised HSC *school registration and home schooling.
NESA is also the NSW test administration authority for [[NAPLAN]].
NESA is responsible for awarding the secondary school credentials [[Record of School Achievement]] and [[Higher School Certificate (New South Wales)|Higher School Certificate]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://educationstandards.nsw.edu.au/wps/portal/nesa/11-12/hsc/about-HSC|title=ABOUT THE HSC|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
